verbs.description: outsteam (third-person singular simple present outsteams, present participle outsteaming, simple past and past participle outsteamed)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To travel further or faster by steam power.
examples: He fully believed that he could outsteam the vessels to the south-east, and, once past these, he knew that he would be in touch with the British ships at the next station before any harm could come to him.
